1. Version 0.2

- Review the timeout event on get_esme_session

- Don't like current PDU packing/unpacking mechanism using the pdu_type/1 
  function.

  Consider creating a pack/unpack function for each PDU type. Call the 
  appropriate pack/unpack function by means of the command_id and remove 
  pdu_type/1 function.

- Put the command_id back into the PDU descriptor.

- Assign default values to standard parameters in smpp_param.hrl (just like
  for TLVs).

- Automatically add/remove trailing '\0' in C-Octet Strings.

  Pay special attention to C-Octet String parameteres defined as composites
  (records), such us TIME_DOMAIN.

- Make OSERL behaviours OTP compilant.  

  Notice the  behavior(name) vs behaviour_info/1 

- Remove unused (commented out) macros from hrls.


2. Version 1.0

- Implement a gen_mc_session behavior.

- Implement a gen_mc behavior.


3. Version 2.0

- Implement a gen_re behavior.



